{"title":"jQuery - check minimal required version","date":"2012-01-24T00:00:00.000Z","tags":"jquery","intro":"<h1 id=\"jquery-check-minimal-required-version\">jQuery - check minimal required version</h1>\n<p>To check whether jQuery is loaded to the page and verify minimum version:</p>\n<pre><code><div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span class=\"k\">if</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"k\">typeof</span> <span class=\"nx\">jQuery</span> <span class=\"o\">==</span> <span class=\"s1\">&#39;undefined&#39;</span> <span class=\"o\">||</span>\n<span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"sr\">/[1-9]\\.[3-9].[1-9]/</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">test</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nx\">$</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">fn</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">jquery</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"k\">throw</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">&#39;jQuery version 1.3.1 or above is required&#39;</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</pre></div>\n\n</code></pre>"}
